---
version: 1
op: value.detect_contradiction
description: does this candidate conflict with any prior, and which ones
max_output_tokens: 80
vars: [candidate, priors]
---
Decide whether the candidate CONTRADICTS any prior statement. A contradiction = priors recommend X while candidate recommends NOT-X (or vice versa) on the SAME topic. Different topics ≠ contradiction.

Candidate: {{.candidate}}

Priors (one per line, ID-prefixed):
{{.priors}}

Output ONLY a JSON object — no prose, no markdown fence:
{"conflicts": true|false, "conflicts_with": ["id1", ...], "why": "≤10 words"}

Examples:
{"conflicts":true,"conflicts_with":["p_2"],"why":"p_2 says avoid X, candidate uses X"}
{"conflicts":false,"conflicts_with":[],"why":"different topics"}
